<taxonomicName id="4C3280D5FFD07F6BFEE1F24AFDEAB21C" box="[373,625,1094,1120]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="berteroana">
<emphasis id="B9462744FFD07F6BFEE1F24AFDEAB21C" box="[373,625,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Callitriche berteroana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingRegion id="49F635B4FFD07F6BFC81F24AFC13B21C" box="[789,904,1094,1120]" country="Chile" name="Araucania" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Araucanía</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49F635B4FFD07F6BFC2BF24AFBAEB21C" box="[959,1077,1094,1120]" country="Chile" name="Valparaiso" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Valparaíso</collectingRegion>
Provinces in 
<collectingCountry id="F325BBC6FFD07F6BFB44F24AFA94B21C" box="[1232,1295,1094,1120]" name="Chile" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Chile</collectingCountry>
, with a single record from the Juan Fernández Islands. Known altitudinal range: 
<quantity id="4CCA56B3FFD07F6BFCFBF266FC5CB2F9" box="[879,967,1130,1157]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" unit="m" value="1200.0">1200 m</quantity>
. See map on page 
<quantity id="4CCA56B3FFD07F6BFB0CF266FB44B2F8" box="[1176,1247,1130,1156]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.9022" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" unit="in" value="193.0">193 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA386A7FFD07F6BFB72F267FA12B2F9" author="Fassett, N. C." box="[1254,1417,1130,1157]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" pagination="209 - 222" refId="ref29059" refString="Fassett, N. C. (1951) Callitriche in the New World. Rhodora 53: 137 - 155, 161 - 182, 185 - 194, 209 - 222, plates 1167 - 1175." type="journal article" year="1951">Fassett (1951)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8DFB56FFD07F6BFF29F282FF65B390" blockId="8.[136,1452,806,2093]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="B9462744FFD07F6BFF29F282FE92B2D4" bold="true" box="[189,265,1166,1192]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Notes:</emphasis>
—The earliest appearance of this entity was in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA386A7FFD07F6BFC8AF283FC63B2D4" author="von Steudel, E. G." box="[798,1016,1166,1193]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" refId="ref31432" refString="von Steudel, E. G. (1840) Nomenclator botanicus, 2 nd ed., vol. 1. J. G. Cotta, Stuttgart and Tubingen, 852 pp." type="book" year="1840">von Steudel (1840)</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName id="4C3280D5FFD07F6BFBB7F282FAAEB2D4" authorityName="von Steudel" authorityYear="1840" box="[1059,1333,1166,1192]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="berteroniana">
<emphasis id="B9462744FFD07F6BFBB7F282FAAEB2D4" box="[1059,1333,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Callitriche berteroniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; however, this name was not validly published because it lacked a diagnosis and a description (Arts. 38.1 and 38.3 of the 
<emphasis id="B9462744FFD07F6BFAF4F2BEFA00B2B0" box="[1376,1435,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Code</emphasis>
). Von Steudel did, however, provide information on a gathering (“ 
<collectingCountry id="F325BBC6FFD07F6BFCE0F2DAFC2AB28C" box="[884,945,1238,1264]" name="Chile" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Chili</collectingCountry>
” and “ 
<emphasis id="B9462744FFD07F6BFB91F2DBFBA6B28C" box="[1029,1085,1239,1264]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Bert.</emphasis>
hrb. nr. 141”), which was later the basis for the first validly published name for this entity: 
<taxonomicName id="4C3280D5FFD07F6BFCDFF2F7FB07B368" authorityName="Hegelmaier" authorityYear="1867" box="[843,1180,1274,1301]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="marginata" variety="berteroana">
<emphasis id="B9462744FFD07F6BFCDFF2F7FC78B368" box="[843,995,1275,1301]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">C. marginata</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B9462744FFD07F6BFBB5F2F6FB07B368" box="[1057,1180,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">berteroana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA386A7FFD07F6BFB40F2F6FA30B369" author="Hegelmaier, C. F." box="[1236,1451,1274,1301]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" pagination="1 - 41" refId="ref29459" refString="Hegelmaier, C. F. (1867) Zur Systematik von Callitriche. Verhandlungen des botanischen Vereins fur die Provinz Brandenburg und die angrenzenden Lander 9: 1 - 41, 1 plate." type="book chapter" year="1867">Hegelmaier (1867)</bibRefCitation>
who provided the following information on the type: “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C3280D5FFD07F6BFD60F313FC49B345" authority="Bert." authorityName="Bert." box="[756,978,1310,1337]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="autumnalis">
<emphasis id="B9462744FFD07F6BFD60F313FC09B344" box="[756,914,1310,1337]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">C. autumnalis</emphasis>
Bert.
</taxonomicName>
in sched. 
<emphasis id="B9462744FFD07F6BFBD3F313FB74B344" box="[1095,1263,1311,1337]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">C. Berteroiana</emphasis>
Steud. Herb. (et Nomencl.)” and “ 
<emphasis id="B9462744FFD07F6BFEC4F34EFEC5B320" box="[336,350,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">β</emphasis>
kommt in 
<collectingCountry id="F325BBC6FFD07F6BFE4EF34EFD8CB320" box="[474,535,1346,1372]" name="Chile" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Chile</collectingCountry>
vor („in spongiosis humidis mont. La Leona 1828, Oct. fl. et fr.” Herb. Steud.)”. Hegelmaier therefore made an unequivocal reference to von Steudel’s name. The 
<typeStatus id="548945F4FFD07F6BFBB6F36AFB1FB3FC" box="[1058,1156,1382,1408]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">holotype</typeStatus>
was located at P (barcode P00697226). We should remark that 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA386A7FFD07F6BFDB4F387FD6CB3D8" author="Fassett, N. C." box="[544,759,1418,1445]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" pagination="209 - 222" refId="ref29059" refString="Fassett, N. C. (1951) Callitriche in the New World. Rhodora 53: 137 - 155, 161 - 182, 185 - 194, 209 - 222, plates 1167 - 1175." type="journal article" year="1951">Fassett (1951: 192)</bibRefCitation>
transferred this entity to the infraspecific sphere of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3280D5FFD07F6BFAA2F387FD92B3B4" authority="(Hegelm.) Fassett (1951: 191 - 194" authorityName="Fassett" authorityYear="1951" baseAuthorityName="Hegelm." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lechleri">
<emphasis id="B9462744FFD07F6BFAA2F387FA37B3D8" box="[1334,1452,1418,1445]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">C. lechleri</emphasis>
(Hegelm.) 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA386A7FFD07F6BFE94F3A3FD92B3B4" author="Fassett, N. C." box="[256,521,1454,1481]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" pagination="209 - 222" refId="ref29059" refString="Fassett, N. C. (1951) Callitriche in the New World. Rhodora 53: 137 - 155, 161 - 182, 185 - 194, 209 - 222, plates 1167 - 1175." type="journal article" year="1951">Fassett (1951: 191–194</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, t. 1174[18]), and listed isotypes (“ 
<emphasis id="B9462744FFD07F6BFC18F3A3FB8AB3B4" box="[908,1041,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Bertero 141</emphasis>
(ISOTYPE of 
<emphasis id="B9462744FFD07F6BFB08F3A3FAD9B3B4" box="[1180,1346,1455,1481]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">C. Berteroiana</emphasis>
Steud.— GH, MO)”).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8DFB56FFD07F6BFF29F3FAFDE8B094" blockId="8.[136,1452,806,2093]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">
<taxonomicName id="4C3280D5FFD07F6BFF29F3FAFE27B06C" box="[189,444,1526,1552]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="berteroana">
<emphasis id="B9462744FFD07F6BFF29F3FAFE27B06C" box="[189,444,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Callitriche berteroana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from all other 
<taxonomicName id="4C3280D5FFD07F6BFD50F3FAFC02B06C" box="[708,921,1526,1552]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B9462744FFD07F6BFD50F3FAFCA6B06C" box="[708,829,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Callitriche</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in South America by its combination of fruit which are broader than long and broadlY winged throughout, some fruit on all specimens with pedicels &lt;
<quantity id="4CCA56B3FFD07F6BFA83F016FAF6B049" box="[1303,1389,1562,1589]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.2" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" unit="mm" value="6.2">6.2 mm</quantity>
long, combined with the presence of stem and leaf scales. It most closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C3280D5FFD07F6BFC63F033FAF2B025" authority="Torrey (1856: 135)" authorityName="Torrey" authorityPageNumber="135" authorityYear="1856" box="[1015,1385,1598,1625]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marginata">
<emphasis id="B9462744FFD07F6BFC63F033FB17B024" box="[1015,1164,1599,1625]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">C. marginata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA386A7FFD07F6BFB06F033FAF2B025" author="Torrey, J." box="[1170,1385,1598,1625]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" pagination="61 - 184" refId="ref31615" refString="Torrey, J. (1856) Description of the general botanical collections. In: United States War Department (Org.) Explorations and surveys for a railroad route from the Mississippi River to the Pacific Ocean, part 5, No. 4. United States War Department, Washington, pp. 61 - 184, 25 plates. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 11139" type="book chapter" year="1856">Torrey (1856: 135)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs in the fruit which are longer, from 
<taxonomicName id="4C3280D5FFD07F6BFD5DF06FFCDAB000" authorityName="Fassett" authorityYear="1951" baseAuthorityName="Hegelm." box="[713,833,1634,1661]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lechleri">
<emphasis id="B9462744FFD07F6BFD5DF06FFCDAB000" box="[713,833,1634,1661]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">C. lechleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the consistently broader wing on the fruit and from both in the capacity to develop longer pedicels. It also resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C3280D5FFD07F6BFCF0F08BFEB5B0B8" authority="(Warb. &amp; Eig) Lansdown et al. (2017 a: 92)" authorityName="Lansdown" authorityPageNumber="92" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Warb. &amp; Eig" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="brutia" variety="naftolskyi">
<emphasis id="B9462744FFD07F6BFCF0F08BFC53B0DC" box="[868,968,1670,1697]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">C. brutia</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B9462744FFD07F6BFB94F08AFBF6B0DC" box="[1024,1133,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">naftolskyi</emphasis>
(Warb. &amp; Eig) 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA386A7FFD07F6BFA8FF08AFEB5B0B8" author="Lansdown, R. V. &amp; Bazos, I. &amp; Caria, M. C. &amp; Troia, A. &amp; Wieringa, J. J." pageId="8" pageNumber="93" pagination="91 - 104" refId="ref30075" refString="Lansdown, R. V., Bazos, I., Caria, M. C., Troia, A. &amp; Wieringa, J. J. (2017 a) New distribution and taxonomic information on Callitriche (Plantaginaceae) in the Mediterranean region. Phytotaxa 313 (1): 91 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 313.1.6" type="journal article" year="2017">
Lansdown 
<emphasis id="B9462744FFD07F6BFA03F08BFF05B0B8" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">et al</emphasis>
. (2017a: 92)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs in the broader wing of the fruit and yellow pollen. These differences are sufficient to justify its treatment as a separate species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8DFB56FFD07F6BFF29F0FEFC3FB14C" blockId="8.[136,1452,806,2093]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="B9462744FFD07F6BFF29F0FEFE28B170" bold="true" box="[189,435,1778,1804]" pageId="8" pageNumber="93">Conservation status:</emphasis>
